Open Standard License — S-Coordinate Reference Implementation

S-Coordinate — Structural Coordinate Resolution
Coordinate Visibility Without Blind Spatial Assumption

Legal Status

This license is intended as a permissive Open Standard license for the S-Coordinate reference implementation.
To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, it grants rights similar in spirit to permissive open-source licenses, while preserving truthful representation requirements for the S-Coordinate name and reference implementation.
This is a custom Open Standard license and is not an OSI-approved open-source license unless separately designated.
If any provision is found unenforceable, the remaining provisions remain in effect.

Nature of Release

This is a minimal, self-contained reference implementation.

It is intended to demonstrate a structural coordinate admissibility model — not to represent a full geometry engine, navigation framework, rendering platform, GPS replacement, or spatial infrastructure system.

Behavioral guarantees apply only within the scope of the reference model and its defined structural assumptions.

