Closing Statement

S-Coordinate explores a simple but fundamental idea:

Coordinate visibility emerges deterministically from structure — without requiring blind trust in numerical position, rendering systems, or map-layer assumptions as a prerequisite.

Coordinates may represent position.

Structure determines whether that position becomes admissible reality.

It is released to encourage:

independent validation
real-world testing
safe experimentation

S-Coordinate is offered as a minimal, verifiable reference implementation of that possibility.
